This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection from RGB-D or depth images. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for processing the data. Additionally, the paper mentions the integration of the system into a robotics platform, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of voxelization and proposals for reducing memory requirements and improving efficiency suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of 3D data, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
